Text.Value: It's like being watched over by Queen Vlaakith herself.
If you have news to discuss with the ch'r'ai, head down the corridor to the eastern wing.
What if they don't find the weapon? Do we even know it -
When they find the weapon, they'll go. And things here can be normal again.
Tell me the Inquisition's purpose, or I'll make mince-pulp of you younglings.
Why are the Inquisition here? Tell me, or I'll beat it out of you.
Our queen's eyes and ears. They're her will, incarnate. And right now, they're here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed tone -  combination of fear and awe

Text.Value: If you want to know more, speak to the kith'rak. But don't tell her we sent you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Jumping in, scared but trying to help

Text.Value: No, definitely don't keep your mouth shut - what else do you know?
The Inquisition are here on Queen Vlaakith's orders. They're searching for a weapon that could finally destroy the ghaik.
Most of them are out searching for the weapon. But Ch'r'ai W'wargaz is here.
They're already searching for the weapon. You should report to Inquisitor W'wargaz first.
We? Don't bring me into it - I know when to keep my mouth shut.
You think we're scared of your threats? They're nothing compared to the Inquisitor's wrath.
Qun'irel! The Inquisition have more to worry about than who you talk to in the corridors.
Where can I find the other Inquisitors?
Why don't you try your pretence on the kith'rak? She's down the corridor in the east wing. I'm sure she'll enjoy the performance.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still a bit scared of you, being helpful

Text.Value: Inquisition? What are you talking about?
Forgive me, jhe'stil. I wasn't complaining. I'm honoured to help search -
An istik? But - but - you can't be here! I can't be seen with you! The ch'r'ai -
We heard the kith'rak say... the Inquisition is wasting her time with this search for a weapon...
The kith'rak will welcome news from beyond the crèche. Good news, at least.
Nothing, jhe'stil.
Nothing, ra'stil.

EditorData.NodeContext: Clipped, formal - reporting to a more senior officer

Text.Value: Keep your mouth shut - you're going to get us in deep tsk'va.
We were only talking about what you already know. About the weapon. The one the kith'rak can't find.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cracked under the pressure, desperate to get out of trouble

Text.Value: Leave.
He's down the corridor in the eastern wing, on the other side of the captain's quarters.
See? I told you. Nothing to worry about.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little confused - but slightly excited on the second sentence

Text.Value: You sound pretty afraid of the Inquisition - why?
The kith'rak is very worried about the ghaik threat. Before you came here, discovering what is happening in Moonrise Towers was our main focus.
She's in her quarters, through those doors.
Qun'irel! Look at him. He's clearly not with the Inquisition.
Qun'irel! Look at her. She's clearly not with the Inquisition.
Qun'irel! Look at them. They're clearly not with the Inquisition.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snapping the name but then cautious/defensive towards the player

Text.Value: Inquisitor W'wargaz. The ch'r'ai.
Ch'r'ai W'wargaz.
At ease. I'm just looking for your captain.
I'm with the Inquisition. Tell me what you were gossiping about. Now.
Who's in charge of the inquisition?
They're the darkness at the edge of Queen Vlaakith's light. It's easy to get... lost in their shadow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bitter, hushed - doesn't want to be overheard, "lost" implying killed, or disappear

Text.Value: And I'm not here to harm you, either. Can you tell me more?
Qun'irel!

Synopsis: The player has the chance to talk to a couple of chatty - but wary - gith youths in a corridor in the creche. They establish the fear around the inquisition.
